parameters.name: ClusterType
parameters.description:
The type of the cluster. Valid values:

*   2: Elastic Compute Service (ECS) cluster
*   3: self-managed Kubernetes cluster in Enterprise Distributed Application Service (EDAS)
*   5: Kubernetes cluster

parameters.name: IaasProvider
parameters.description:
The provider of Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) resources that are used in the cluster.

When you use Alibaba Cloud, set the value to `ALIYUN`. The value is case-sensitive.

parameters.name: LogicalRegionId
parameters.description: The ID of the custom namespace. The ID is in the `physical region ID:custom namespace identifier` format. Example: `cn-hangzhou:test`.

parameters.name: NetworkMode
parameters.description:
The network type of the cluster. Valid values:

*   1: classic network
*   2: virtual private cloud (VPC)

parameters.name: OversoldFactor
parameters.description:
**This parameter is deprecated.** The CPU overcommit ratio supported by a Docker cluster. Valid values:

*   2: 1:2, which means that resources are overcommitted by 1:2.
*   4: 1:4, which means that resources are overcommitted by 1:4.
*   8: 1:8, which means that resources are overcommitted by 1:8.

parameters.name: VpcId
parameters.description: The ID of the VPC. This parameter is required if you set the NetworkMode parameter to 2.
